	   <tr><td colspan=2>Went on a Xanamech raid, was the only chanter there (48, yea a bit low, but I helped a lot). Chanters have the job of mezzing the gnome and mem bluring him while everyone gets to the dragon. BE CAREFUL! We were near the dragon when I get the command to let him walk, by the time I started to remezz him after some mobs aggro, he despaswned, unlikely he got killed (less it was by Xanamech himself) because he just diasappeared so quickly from my target window, so I'm 99% sure he's on a timer.<br><br>Beware when mezzing, con him after every mem blur, if he's threatening, keep trying, the little guy hits hard! But with a secondary healer watching your hp and some buffs, I was able to handle him without tash and not too many resists, though he was high yellow to me.<br><br>My advice is to have a group or 2 clear ahead before the turn in so that you dont waste a lot of time, him despawning will disappoint a lot of ppl!<br>&nbsp;<br>You have slain Chief Ry'Gorr!<br>You Shout: Woo!<br>A Ry'Gorr Avenger hits YOU for 300 points of damage!<br>LOADING, PLEASE WAIT...<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=548452&alt=14355" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=548452&alt=14355</a></td></tr>
