	   <tr><td colspan=2>Our guild killed him last night with a force of 36. He is a fun fight. His AoE's do indeed seem irresistable. Keeping the gnome safe is not too bad if your party can keep aggro on the MA, and have MA position the dragon so gnome is always behind him. Remember the MA will more than likely be snared from the dragon's AoE. He seems to use stun more toward the end of the fight, in our experience.<br><br>The gnome will attack anyone in wolf form, also, AoE's should not be used either for same reason (obviously). He can be rooted and mem-blurred without problems BEFORE he spawns the dragon. Do not do it after. We used this tactic and everyone recieved factory flag from him without incident.<br>&nbsp;<br><a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=40700 target=_new>Mjolinir</a><br>Grave Lord of Innoruuk<br>Lost Boys<br>Bertoxxulous</td></tr>
