	   <tr><td colspan=2>Tried this guy a couple days ago. 53 People in raid, average level 57 = total wipe, everyone dead. We got it down about 1/3 but the AE spells were just too much for us to deal with. <br><br>My suggestions: <br><br>1. 60 people with average level of 60 is about the minimum I would guess for this fight.<br><br>2. Don't bother bringing your resist gear, his AE attacks are completely unresistable, every single person in the raid was hit for full damage every time.<br><br>3. Had no problem spawning him, just clear the path about halfway up, hand in the items, and mez/memblur the little guy every time you have to clear some mobs. He never warped or tried to walk back to his hut.<br><br>4. Have your clerics and paladins use their group heals, by the time they get one CH off for the tank, the rest of the group will most likely be dead.<br>&nbsp;<br>~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>Baron Geryn Silverdragon<br>61 Shaman of Bristlebane<br>16AA and counting...<br>~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~</td></tr>
