	   <tr><td colspan=2>Or instead of 60 people at lvl 60 you get 35-40 people at avg lvl 60 who know what they are doing?&nbsp;&nbsp;I hate Zerg mentality.<br><br>Did him last night with 42 people, raid avg lvl 61, and my guild is NToV level.  We lost one person during the whole fight.  I would consider the dragon on par with an average NToV fight like Aaryonar or Kreizen.<br><br>For some real tips:<br><br>1.  DO NOT USE CH.  His AE is also a stun, and using 10 second heals is like unzipping your fly.  Spam heal with high lvl remedies and natures touch, etc.  Get spell haste and focus items to help make sure you are not as vulnerable.<br><br>2.  Group heals, keep your groups above 50% health so that low hp doesn't screw up aggro management.<br><br>3.  Keep the dragon facing away from the gnome.  You cannot use mez/charm on the gnome during the fight or it will break the quest and you will not get flags, so you have to look out for his well being.  If the dragon enrages and is facing the gnome, the gnome will suicide on ripostes.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
