	   <a name=103990614440826></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f103990614440826><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=search.shtml?id=10234&mid=103990614440826>Dropped him last night</a> <a id=fs8 href=search.shtml?id=10234&mid=103990614440826#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=111408><span id=Sage>melbin</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>50 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Dec 14th 6:13 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.81]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Xanamech finally went down to us last night.&nbsp;&nbsp;3rd time, first 2 attempts were wipes.  We had 42 people in the raid, average level 60.<br><br>There were several key things required to get this done.<br><br>1) Keep the gnome on track to get him to the garage.  Sometimes you have to root him and mem blur to get him to stop attacking every single wandering robot in the zone.  Stay out of his path, or sometimes the diversions he takes to go around obstacles are roundabout and undesirable.<br><br>2) Kill the adds in the garage before awakening the dragon.  Then awaken Xanamech before the adds repop, which happened in about 10 minutes I would estimate.<br><br>3) Keep the MA alive.  Sounds obvious, but since Xanamech has AoE stun, you may just find yourself with nobody capable of casting CH on your MA before he dies.  I recommend stationing a Paladin directly behind MA to LoH 3 seconds after the battle starts.<br><br>4) Slow him.  A 62 shaman was able to land slow in about 10 seconds.  Your mileage may vary, good luck, because success/failure depends on this.<br><br>5) Keep the gnome alive.  The gnome is pretty tough... he can take lots of shots from the dragon, but if you don't take precautions, he will die, and you will end up flagless.  Our strategy was to keep the dragon pointed away from him, to stop the gnome from riposting himself to death.  Another strategy is to sacrifice a druid, who keeps him rooted during the entire battle.  Druid will have to die from the aggro, because you CAN NOT MEM BLUR GNOME DURING DRAGON FIGHT OR YOU WILL NOT GET FLAGGED, but a quick rez can fix this.<br><br>6) Bring several epic clerics.  You will have 12 minutes after the battle to get everyone rezzed so that they can get their flags.  Might be tough to do without manaless rezzing.<br><br>Good luck.  He dropped the Cord Hilted Spike Driver and the Woven Shim Shoker for us.  Good loot day for warriors and other melee, bad loot day for casters.<br>&nbsp;<br>----<br><br>Baron Wozan K`Tang, 62 Erudite Shadow Knight<br>Vass Grassbender, 54 Wood Elf Druid<br>Melbin, 51 Barbarian Warrior<br>&lt;Divine Prophecy&gt; -- Xev</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
